{"_comment": "config/qa-pool/pool.jsonl — the QA bot pool (host-only, never committed). One JSON object PER LINE (JSONL). Copy to pool.jsonl in this folder (gitignored) and fill with REAL staging bot tokens. `yard qa-pool seed` pushes it into the yard and admin/adds each entry; re-seeding is idempotent (deduped by note). Add one entry per concurrent dev-agent you want to support — N entries => N agents lease DIFFERENT bots, no Telegram 409. Lines whose only key is _comment are ignored. NEVER put a PROD bot here. Each entry: {kind, payload, note?}."}
{"kind": "telegram", "note": "staging-bot-1", "payload": {"groupId": "-1001234567890", "driverToken": "<DRIVER_BOT_TOKEN_1>", "sutToken": "<SUT_BOT_TOKEN_1>"}}
{"kind": "telegram", "note": "staging-bot-2", "payload": {"groupId": "-1001234567890", "driverToken": "<DRIVER_BOT_TOKEN_2>", "sutToken": "<SUT_BOT_TOKEN_2>"}}
